\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. S. origanifolia} (Lam.) Baillon, {\i Hist. Pl.}{\b  9}: 288 (1888). Stems flexuous, angled, pubescent, woody below. Leaves 1·5-2·5(-5) × 1-2(-4) cm, ovate-rhombic to suborbicular, entire, sparsely pubescent, narrowed into petiole of equal length. Pedicels nodding. Calyx 3-4 mm, divided almost to base; lobes subulate. Corolla 6-10 mm, whitish, densely lanate below insertion of stamens. Berry 1-1·5 cm, ovoid, creamy-white, edible; seeds 1·5-2 mm, hairy.{\i  Locally naturalized in S. & S.W. Europe.} [Az Br Co Ga Hs It Lu.] ({\i E. temperate South America}.)
